    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix PDCCH allocation to UL frame mapping in TDD configurations\n\n### Summary\nThe `pdcchalloc2ulframe()` function in the MAC scheduler was returning incorrect UL frame numbers for TDD configurations. When processing PDCCH allocations in certain subframes, the function would incorrectly calculate the corresponding UL frame, leading to scheduling conflicts and missed UL transmissions.\n\nThis issue was particularly noticeable in TDD subframe assignment 1 and 6, where the timing relationship between PDCCH allocation and PUSCH transmission is non-standard. The original implementation used a simplified frame increment logic that didn't account for the actual UL subframe calculation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Rewrote `pdcchalloc2ulframe()` to properly calculate UL frame based on subframe wraparound\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Made function consistent with `pdcchalloc2ulsubframe()` logic\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Enhanced logging to show both UL frame and subframe\n\n"
}